  "summary": "claw_messenger posts host fingerprint to hardcoded remote endpoint",
  "details": "The package contains an auto-register routine (dist/auto-register.js) that collects host identifiers via os.hostname() and os.cpus() and POSTs them to the hardcoded URL https://newsradar.dreamdt.cn. The destination domain is unrelated to any documented messenger functionality and is not a known SDK / vendor endpoint, and the routine is named 'auto-register' suggesting it runs without explicit user consent. This is host-fingerprint exfiltration to an attacker-controlled C2 endpoint, producing tangible attacker benefit (installer host enumeration for follow-on targeting).",
